## 1. Two-thread architecture

### What runs where

| Operation | Thread |
|-----------|--------|
| `node.name`, mutations, `fetch`, `figma.clientStorage` | main (`dist/code.js`) |
| `figma.getNodeByIdAsync`, `getMainComponentAsync`, `loadFontAsync`, `figma.codegen` | main |
| `document.getElementById`, rendering, `sessionStorage` (session-only) | UI (`ui.html`) |

### Never do this

```js
// ❌ UI iframe — CORS / ReferenceError
fetch("https://api.openai.com/...")
figma.currentPage.selection

// ❌ postMessage — nodes are not structured-cloneable
figma.ui.postMessage({ node: someSceneNode })
```

### Node lookup helper (main thread)

```js
async function getNodeById(id) {
  if (!id) return null;
  return await figma.getNodeByIdAsync(id);
}
```

Every caller of `getNodeById` must be `async` and `await` it (propagate through `figma.ui.onmessage`).

### Async classification chain

`gatherContext` is **async** and must **`await deepChildScan`**. Skipping `await` empties chevron/sibling signals → accordion misclassified as tablist.

```js
// ✓ for-loop + await — never forEach(async ...)
for (let i = 0; i < node.children.length; i++) {
  const sub = await deepChildScan(child, maxDepth, depth + 1);
  mergeDeepScanResults(result, sub);
}

const ctx = await gatherContext(rootNode);
const detection = detectComponent(ctx, rootNode);
```

Callers that must `await gatherContext`: `analyzeNodeAndPost`, `ANALYZE_SELECTION`, `RESCAN_NODE`, `collectScanCandidates`, autofix paths that need context.

**`deepChildScan` default `maxDepth` is 3** (see `dist/code.js`). Performance guidance elsewhere may say 5 for generic traversal — do not contradict the implemented default without changing code.

