## 2. Plugin API patterns

### Traversal — performance

```js
// ✗ document-wide
figma.currentPage.findAll(...)

// ✓ scoped
frame.findAllWithCriteria({ types: ["TEXT", "INSTANCE"] })
```

Yield on large batches: `await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 0))` every ~20 nodes.

### Guards

- `absoluteBoundingBox` may be **null** (collapsed components) — always check
- `isNodeVisible(node)` — skip hidden subtrees (not in a11y tree)
- `isA11yGeneratedLayer(node)` — skip plugin-created layers (see §8)

### Plugin data

```js
node.setPluginData("a11y.role", "button")           // this plugin only
node.setSharedPluginData("a11y", "role", "button") // Dev Mode + other plugins
```

Use shared keys consistently for codegen (`persistCodegenHandoffFields` in code). Prefer kebab-case attribute names in handoff where the codegen layer expects them.

### Undo

Batch canvas mutations: `figma.commitUndo()` once per user-initiated apply (single undo step). Individual **Fix automatically** clicks also commit undo in `autoFixIssue`.

