## 3. Figma file semantics

### Layer naming (ARIA-aligned)

```
button / submit [aria-label="Submit form"]
input / email [type=email, required]
dialog / confirm-delete [aria-modal=true]
radio-group / payment [role=radiogroup]
accordion-item / faq-1
  heading / faq-1-title [aria-level=3]
  button / faq-1-trigger [aria-expanded=false]
  panel / faq-1-panel [role=region]
```

Semantic layer names for plugin-created structure: `label`, `input`, `trigger`, `panel`, `tab-list`, `tab`, `tab-panel`, `close-button`, `visually-hidden-label`, etc. See `docs/fix-non-component-element-briefing.md` for full builders.

### Auto-layout = structure

- **Vertical** AL → block-level (fields, accordion items, form stacks)
- **Horizontal** AL → inline (checkbox+label, button groups, tabs)
- Child order = reading order = tab order: `label → control → hint → error`
- Do not use absolute positioning for semantically ordered interactive content

### Variants = ARIA states

| Variant property | ARIA / CSS |
|------------------|------------|
| State=Focus | `:focus-visible` / focus ring |
| State=Disabled | `aria-disabled` |
| State=Error | `aria-invalid` |
| Checked / Selected / Expanded | `aria-checked` / `aria-selected` / `aria-expanded` |

### Semantic root

When the user selects one star, radio, or tab, analyze **`getSemanticRoot(selection)`**, not the leaf. Stop at `_a11y_*` generated parents. Implementation: `dist/code.js`.

