## 4. Accessibility principles

### WCAG 2.2 AA — always audit

| Criterion | Requirement | Typical severity |
|-----------|-------------|------------------|
| 1.4.3 | Text contrast ≥ 4.5:1 (3:1 large) | HIGH |
| 1.4.11 | Non-text UI contrast ≥ 3:1 | HIGH |
| 1.4.1 | Not color-only | HIGH / MANUAL |
| 2.4.7 | Focus visible | HIGH |
| 2.5.3 | Label in name | HIGH |
| 2.5.8 | Touch target ≥ 24×24 (44×44 recommended) | HIGH |
| 3.3.2 | Input labels | HIGH |
| 4.1.2 | Name, role, value | HIGH |

Report human-only judgment as `{ severity: "MANUAL", message: "Verify manually: …" }`.

### ARIA APG — structural highlights

- **Accordion:** `heading` → `button[aria-expanded]` → `region` panel. Never `button` wrapping `heading`.
- **Dialog:** `role=dialog`, `aria-modal`, labelled heading, close control with accessible name.
- **Combobox:** chevron decorative (`aria-hidden`); listbox + options when open.
- **Icon-only controls:** require accessible name (`aria-label` or visible hidden label).
- **Star rating:** `radiogroup`; each star named (e.g. "2 stars").

