## 6. NON_COMPONENT_ELEMENT — three paths

When an interactive node is a Frame/Group instead of a Component/Instance:

```
NON_COMPONENT_ELEMENT on node
│
├── PATH A — AUTO (leaf / simple)
│   Plugin creates component + variants off-canvas, swaps instance in place
│
├── PATH B — AUTO (uniform children)
│   Loop children; componentize each leaf/simple child (same PATH A logic per child)
│
└── PATH C — FIGMA_AI (complex: mixed form, dialog, etc.)
    Targeted prompt with exact nodeId, child ids, role, required variants
    UI capability = FIGMA_AI; designer runs Figma AI manually
```

**UI rule:** Only **PATH C** uses the Figma AI button. PATH A/B run through plugin handlers (`fixLinkToComponent` / future `fixNonComponentElement` builders — see `docs/fix-non-component-element-briefing.md`) when the user chooses **Fix automatically** or linking flow, not a generic "convert to component" prompt.

PATH C prompts **must** include: `nodeId`, `nodeName`, current structure, required variants (Default/Hover/Focus/Disabled…), ARIA role, and child `nodeId`s to preserve.

PATH A/B creation rules:

- Build master **off canvas** (e.g. `x + 4000`) — do not clutter the artboard
- `figma.combineAsVariants` for state sets; set `.description` with Role / States / HTML / APG URL
- Replace original with **Default** instance; tag `setSharedPluginData("a11y", …)`
- Inter fonts only; `await loadFontAsync` before text

Current linking fallback (`fixLinkToComponent`): search existing components → link instance → if none, fall back to PATH C prompt.

