## 8. UI thread (`ui.html`)

### Selection state (do not regress)

```js
selectionState = {
  lastScannedNodeId,
  lastScannedResults,
  currentSelection,
}
```

| State | Preview | Results |
|-------|---------|---------|
| No selection, no scan | "Select a layer to begin" | Empty |
| No selection, has last scan | Placeholder | Last results + badge "Showing last scan · [name]" + Re-scan |
| Selection, not scanned | Layer preview image | Last scan (if any) with badge, else empty |
| Selection = last scanned | Preview image | Live results |
| Scan in progress | Preview + loading | Loading (clear cache at scan start via `beginNewScan`) |

- **No** duplicate "Select a layer" in the results panel
- **No** "Scan this layer" button — use header **Start Analysis**
- Deselect **does not** clear `lastScannedResults`
- **Re-scan** → `RESCAN_NODE` (selects node on canvas, runs analysis)

### Designer-facing copy

- Use `CHECK_DISPLAY_NAMES` — never raw matrix IDs in issue cards
- Hide dev-only ARIA dumps from designer view; show in Dev Mode / codegen
- Issue actions driven by `issue.capability` only

### postMessage types (extend in code when adding features)

`ANALYZE_SELECTION`, `RESCAN_NODE`, `AUTO_FIX_ISSUE`, `APPLY_FIXES`, `APPLY_WITH_MODE`, `SAVE_API_KEY`, `ASK_ANSWER`, `EXPORT_PREVIEW`, `SELECTION_CHANGED`, `SELECTION_CLEARED`, `ANALYSIS_RESULTS`, …

