## 9. Dev Mode

When `editorType === 'dev'`:

- Read-only for fixes — no Apply Fixes on canvas
- Show role, ARIA attributes, issues, WCAG references
- Technology-agnostic handoff (not HTML snippets in designer audit)
- Code tab via `figma.codegen` + shared plugin data namespace `a11y`

---

## 10. AI usage

- Default model: **gpt-4o-mini** (settings in UI)
- Rule engine first; AI for MED/LOW classification and label generation when API key present
- Input cap ~800 chars context; short label output (~100 chars max for generated labels)
- Cache in pluginData where implemented — avoid repeat calls for unchanged nodes
- Vision only when tiebreak / unknown role requires it (`AI_LOADING` phases)

---

## 11. Accordion classification (avoid false positives)

Treat as accordion only when **all** hold:

1. Chevron/expand indicator co-located with row text (subtree depth ≤ 2 per row)
2. Outer layout **VERTICAL**
3. No strong counter-signals: horizontal-only bar, pill chips, tab-bar naming

Log `[accordion] rowsWithChevron` when debugging. Counter-signals zero out accordion score.

---

## 12. What to ask the designer (before ambiguous fixes)

- Heading level for accordion/dialog in context
- Button vs link behavior
- `alertdialog` vs `dialog` for destructive flows
- Accordion single vs multiple expand
- Chip: removable / selectable / display-only
- Error message copy for inputs
- Icon-only: is tooltip the accessible name?

Queue ASK questions; do not open multiple modals at once.

